version_description: This version includes the lead guitar and the second guitar. This version also can be played on classic guitar.

song_name: I Was A Fool To Care
I Was A Fool To Care

version_description: This isn't perfect but yeah just give it a go and maybe add some suggestions. Throughout (and during the chorus especially) use a lot of palm muting. Often just play the low strings and occasionally let the high ones ring out closer to the end of each chord/chorus. Added the full chords so you can choose to play all the notes but also mute when necessary, cheers and take it easy.
It is the Demo version / an alternate version.
It has the chords over the lyrics which makes it easier for begginers to sing along.
It's exactly as Mac plays it but without the capo.
Standard tuning but with the tuner set 452Hz.
This version offers a different style of Mac DeMarcos hit song, this version is also similar to the rhythm guitar that is played in the song.

Based off the first guitar in the studio version (https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wIuBcb2T55Q) (not the melodic guitar), explained in a tutorial in youtube (https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zOMvQInqPl4). Capo on 2nd fret, standard tuning.
